==English==
===Noun===
'''trunk''' (''plural:'' [[trunks]])

# the (usually single) upright part of a [[tree]], between the [[root]]s and the [[branch]]es.
# a large [[suitcase]], usually requiring two persons to lift and with a hinged [[lid]].
# [[torso]].
# the [[extended]] and [[articulated]] [[nose]] or [[nasal]] [[organ]] of an [[elephant]].
# (''US'') the luggage storage compartment of a [[sedan]]/[[saloon]] style car.
# a telecommunications line.

==== Synonyms ====
*[[boot]] (5, ''British'', ''Aus'')
*[[torso]] (3)

====Related terms====
*[[tree trunk]]

